I would not choose sensu:6.11.0 for the Graviton migration unless you have a strong compatibility reason.

Use this instead:

image: sensu/sensu:6.14.0

or, if your org wants a less aggressive upgrade:

image: sensu/sensu:6.13.1

Reason: Sensu’s current supported-version table lists 6.14.0, 6.13.1, 6.13.0, and 6.12.0 as supported, while 6.11.0 is marked not supported. Sensu 6.11.0 was released on January 31, 2024, so it is not the version I’d pick for a fresh architecture migration in 2026. 

Also, Sensu’s platform docs show Linux arm64 support for the backend, agent, and CLI in binary distributions, and Docker images are available for Sensu backend + agent as Linux containers. 

Important correction

The image should be:

sensu/sensu:6.14.0

not:

sensu:6.11.0

unless sensu:6.11.0 is your own internally mirrored image name.

Before changing Git, verify ARM64 manifest

Run:

docker buildx imagetools inspect sensu/sensu:6.14.0

You should see both:

linux/amd64
linux/arm64

Also test the exact candidate version:

docker buildx imagetools inspect sensu/sensu:6.13.1
docker buildx imagetools inspect sensu/sensu:6.14.0

My recommendation for your STG branch

Use 6.14.0 in STG if you are comfortable upgrading Sensu during this migration:

images:
  - name: sensu/sensu
    newTag: 6.14.0

Then add ARM scheduling in your Kustomize overlay:

nodeSelector:
  kubernetes.io/arch: arm64

tolerations:
  - key: graviton
    operator: Equal
    value: "true"
    effect: NoSchedule

When would I use 6.11.0?

Only if all of these are true:

1. Your current backend is already on Sensu 6.11.0.
2. You want to avoid a Sensu version upgrade during the Graviton migration.
3. docker buildx imagetools inspect sensu/sensu:6.11.0 shows linux/arm64.
4. Your Sensu assets/plugins also support arm64.

Otherwise, for a clean STG migration to Graviton, I’d use:

sensu/sensu:6.14.0

and validate all Sensu Asset resources for linux/arm64 before moving the pods to Graviton nodes.